messages.message:
Hey, just tested this now. The display is so much better than us converting sheets to PDF during processing.

I read the document which talks about the architecture behind this with the TDF. Should this display also improve the extraction quality too if we’re using the new framework?
One minor nit, my sheet goes up to column G, but we show another un named unselectable column to the right of it. Is that expected?
When you go to the grid view, you get an endless spinner, I guess this is because there isn’t a thumbnail to show - but we should put something else in there, or make a thumbnail
Another minor thing, there are a few cells we seem to be handling differently to excel, below is a screenshot from excel, this is in IB.
Overall though this is great, massive improvement :clap:
Minor design thing, these buttons look really similar to the data in the sheet, this meant I didn’t actually notice they were there.
We have not yet done the benchmarking, the backend changes are in progress

I’ll start one more round of testing of excels on thjs
